  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 04:47 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] V4 VWAP Relaxation Backtest + Deployment Patch Ready\n\n**Task:** Quantify VWAP filter impact precisely. Build deployable V4 patch for Monday active hours.\n\n**Finding:**\n- VWAP blocks at peak hours over 9 trading days:\n  - **11h: 63% block rate** (12 blocked, 7 executed). At 88% WR \u2192 $93.80 missed.\n  - **12h: 30% block rate** (8 blocked, 19 executed). At 82% WR \u2192 $53.60 missed.\n  - **19h: 5% block rate** (1 blocked). Minimal impact.\n  - **20h: 33% block rate** (6 blocked). At 58% WR \u2192 $9.30 missed (marginal).\n- **Total: $161.80 missed over 9 days = ~$18/day.**\n- VWAP-blocked signals have legitimate parameters: bias -27 to -54, PM prices 0.455-0.515, entry delays 134-274s. These look like real trades, not noise.\n\n**My thinking:** The VWAP all-hours stats (54% vs 45%) are misleading because they average across all hours including garbage hours we've already cut. At 11h (88% WR), the London session structural edge dominates \u2014 VWAP disagreement is a lagging indicator that doesn't capture intra-session momentum. At 20h (58% WR), VWAP adds genuine protective value.\n\n**Decision:** V4 patch written and saved to `patches/v4-vwap-relax.patch.md`:\n1. Relax VWAP at 11h/12h (log bypass, don't block)\n2. Keep VWAP mandatory at 19h/20h\n3. Deploy Monday before 11h UTC with reduced position size ($8 vs $11) for first 20 trades\n4. Rollback trigger: WR < 60% over 10 trades at 11h\n\nCombined V4 deployment plan (Monday AM):\n- VWAP relaxation at 11h/12h \u2190 this patch\n- Copy conviction boost \u2192 0 (log only)\n- F&G confidence modifier (from regime_classifier.py)\n\n**Next P2 heartbeat:** Deploy V4 before 11h UTC Monday. Monitor first hour in real-time.\n\n## 2026-03-30 04:43 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Signal is HURTING Performance + PM Bot Restart Loop\n\n**Task:** Run copy-intel-tracker, analyze copy signal correlation with trade outcomes. Fix PM bot stability.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Copy